  "content_markdown": "Version: 8.3Marketing\nOn this page\nYou can manage audience efficiently by using dynamic and static folders to add or exclude contacts from bulk emails without the need for manual filters.\nBefore you start managing audience, **create a corresponding folder** to include or exclude contacts in the **Contacts** section. Learn more: [Folders](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1018). You can also use an existing folder if needed.\n## Add contacts\u200b\nTo **add contacts** :\n1. **Open** the **Bulk emails** section.\n2. **Open** the relevant record.\n3. **Go to** the **Audience** tab \u2192 **Add audience**. This opens a window.\n4. **Select** the needed folder \u2192 **Select**. Creatio will display the number of total contacts, unsubscribed contacts, and hard bounced contacts in the folder.\nIf you select a dynamic folder, the number of contacts might change over time as Creatio applies the folder criteria continuously.\nFig. 1 Add audience\n![Fig.\u00a01 Add audience](https://d3a7ykdi65m4cy.cloudfront.net/ac-en/s3fs-public/images/Marketing_Tools/add_bulk_email_audience/scr_add_audience.png)\n**As a result** , Creatio will add contacts to the recipient list. Each email address will only receive the message once, even if it appears in multiple folders. You will be able to see the exact audience together with responses after the email is sent.\nnote\nLicenses are only spent on **new contacts**. The number of licenses required is calculated **after** the bulk email is sent.\n## Exclude contacts\u200b\nYou can exclude contacts from the email audience, for example, to respect audience preferences or ensure compliance with communication regulations. To do this:\n1. **Open** the **Bulk emails** section.\n2. **Open** the relevant record.\n3. **Go to** the **Audience** tab \u2192 **Exclude**. This opens a window.\n4. **Select** the needed folder \u2192 **Select**. Creatio will display the number of total contacts, unsubscribed contacts, and hard bounced contacts in the folder.\n**As a result** , Creatio will exclude the contacts from the recipient list, even if they are included in the selected audience folder.\n* * *\n## See also\u200b\n[Create a bulk email](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=2545)\n[Marketing email functionality usage policy](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=2546)\n[Add a campaign](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1074)",
